snippet.textDisplay:
Before my stupid skeptic rant that I am completely powerless to prevent, I do want to say I LOVE riding my bike, I usually shoot for 8 - 10 miles out, then the 8 - 10 back, try to find interesting places to go to and plan my route. It's got a great exploration kind of feel to it, and makes getting there feel soooo much more fulfilling. So if anyone is thinking of trying that as well, I highly recommend it! I also happen to apparently accidentally be on the "intermittent fasting" diet, not because I'm dieting, but because I get so distracted and kinda just forget to eat....

COFFEE IS LIFE! BLACK -- ONLY! EVER!


Now I don't wanna be "that guy" but as far as electrical stimulus and cupping goes.... I think the best you can hope for is nerve desensitization which in that case you might as well just hit your toes with a hammer (you know, that old trick that 'distracts' you from one pain with another?) To each his own, definitely, and any alternative treatment, even if it's physically ineffective can be mentally effective and that makes much more of a difference so why am I typing all of this please save me I hate that I have to be this way omgggg
